WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:02:31.460 --> 00:02:36.420
The Gray Terminal

3
00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:40.960
Ten years ago, in the East Blue...

4
00:02:42.860 --> 00:02:48.680
there was a little hamlet known as
Windmill Village, where people lived peacefully.

5
00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:52.700
Not far from there was Mt. Colubo,
where none dared set foot.

6
00:02:53.720 --> 00:03:00.760
There, it was survival of the fittest.
As for the weak, death was all but certain.

7
00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:06.200
Grandpa, I'm telling you...

8
00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:08.470
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates...

9
00:03:08.470 --> 00:03:10.740
What's this King of the Pirates crap?!

10
00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:12.910
L-Let me go!

11
00:03:12.910 --> 00:03:16.780
First you eat that devil fruit,
and now you're spouting nonsense!

12
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:19.220
Luffy! Both you and Ace

13
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:22.050
Monkey D. Garp
(10 Years Ago)

14
00:03:19.220 --> 00:03:22.050
are gonna be strapping Marines!

15
00:03:22.050 --> 00:03:24.100
Ow, ow, ow, dammit!

16
00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:26.830
Monkey D. Luffy
(10 Years Ago)

17
00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:26.470
Why does this hurt when my body is rubber?!

18
00:03:26.470 --> 00:03:28.050
Let me go, Grandpa!

19
00:03:28.830 --> 00:03:32.120
Leaving you in Windmill Village was a mistake!

20
00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:34.590
It just had to be pirates!

21
00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:39.430
What is this place?

22
00:03:40.800 --> 00:03:46.000
Stop that! Say your prayers, whoever you are!

23
00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:47.070
It's me.

24
00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:52.350
M-Mr. Garp!

25
00:03:54.810 --> 00:03:58.280
Curly Dadan

26
00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:01.720
Dogra
Mountain Bandit

27
00:04:01.750 --> 00:04:05.190
Magra
Mountain Bandit

28
00:04:05.190 --> 00:04:06.720
You seem well.

29
00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:11.600
This isn't funny! Please,
you can't do this to me!

30
00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:14.140
That Ace kid is ten years old now!

31
00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:17.770
Oh, already? How is he?

32
00:04:17.770 --> 00:04:19.920
It's not funny!

33
00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:23.730
We can't handle him anymore!
You have to take him back!

34
00:04:23.730 --> 00:04:24.850
Putting that aside...

35
00:04:24.850 --> 00:04:26.780
Don't put it aside!

36
00:04:26.780 --> 00:04:28.680
Will you pipe down, kid?!

37
00:04:28.680 --> 00:04:30.880
I'd like you to look after him, too.

38
00:04:32.380 --> 00:04:34.490
Hey, Luffy. Say hi.

39
00:04:34.490 --> 00:04:35.320
Sup?

40
00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:38.020
Who's the kid?

41
00:04:38.020 --> 00:04:40.660
He's my grandson.

42
00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:41.390
Wha...?

43
00:04:41.390 --> 00:04:43.660
– What?!
– What?!

44
00:04:43.660 --> 00:04:45.280
Another one?!

45
00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:49.840
He's Garp's... I mean, Mr. Garp's grandson?!

46
00:04:49.840 --> 00:04:51.040
– We can't!
– We can't!

47
00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:53.400
All right! Here are your choices:

48
00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:56.510
Spend the rest of your life
in a cell, or raise this kid.

49
00:04:56.510 --> 00:05:00.380
I've turned a blind eye to
who-knows-how-many of your crimes.

50
00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:03.850
– No fair!
– No fair!

51
00:05:03.850 --> 00:05:06.820
Well, I don't wanna get arrested but...

52
00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:12.410
Sometimes I feel like prison might
actually be better than raising Ace.

53
00:05:12.410 --> 00:05:15.100
And now you're saddling
us with your grandson?

54
00:05:15.100 --> 00:05:17.700
I bet this kid's some kind of monster too.

55
00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:19.210
What a crummy shack!

56
00:05:19.210 --> 00:05:21.380
I'll knock you into next week!

57
00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:23.000
He ignored me!

58
00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:23.000
– Boss!
– Boss!

59
00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:24.680
Are you alright?!

60
00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:28.070
What the...? Ugh! It's spit! Gross!

61
00:05:28.720 --> 00:05:29.830
Who's there?!

62
00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:32.440
Hey, you!

63
00:05:33.210 --> 00:05:35.080
Say you're sorry! That was gross!

64
00:05:35.080 --> 00:05:36.720
Hm? Ace!

65
00:05:36.720 --> 00:05:39.510
Oh! Are you back, Ace?!

66
00:05:41.080 --> 00:05:45.320
Portgas D. Ace
(10 Years Ago)

67
00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:46.560
Hey! Say sorry!

68
00:05:48.760 --> 00:05:53.620
Luffy, this is Ace.
He's three years older than you.

69
00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:56.430
Starting today, you'll be living together.

70
00:05:56.440 --> 00:05:57.810
– What?!
– What?!

71
00:05:57.810 --> 00:05:58.900
It's not decided yet!

72
00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:05.710
Be nice!

73
00:06:05.710 --> 00:06:06.810
It is decided?!

74
00:06:06.810 --> 00:06:08.850
Is there a problem?

75
00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:12.980
– Happy to have him!
– Happy to have him!

76
00:06:13.820 --> 00:06:16.690
It's your turn to wash dishes!

77
00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:16.690
More!

78
00:06:17.060 --> 00:06:18.430
Gimme some more, pops!

79
00:06:18.430 --> 00:06:20.590
I'll have you know I'm a woman!

80
00:06:20.590 --> 00:06:23.870
Do you even know where you are now?!

81
00:06:23.870 --> 00:06:24.500
No.

82
00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:25.980
Then I'll tell you.

83
00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:29.840
You're in the den of the Dadan Family,
the mountain bandits of Mt. Colubo!

84
00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:33.570
Mountain bandits? I hate mountain bandits!

85
00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:40.210
Shut it, you brat! We're the ones
who got stuck with a little snot like you!

86
00:06:40.210 --> 00:06:42.320
If you don't like it here, fine!

87
00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:44.870
Get lost and die like a dog!

88
00:06:44.870 --> 00:06:46.580
Take it easy, Boss.

89
00:06:46.580 --> 00:06:48.450
I wanna eat more...

90
00:06:50.120 --> 00:06:52.420
Gimme some of that meat too.

91
00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:03.900
All this meat is from a bison
that Ace took down for us.

92
00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:07.140
He gave us a cut of the haul
so that everyone can eat.

93
00:07:07.140 --> 00:07:09.210
Mountain bandits have it tough.

94
00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:12.050
Starting tomorrow,
I'm gonna work your butt off!

95
00:07:12.050 --> 00:07:16.440
Cleaning, laundry,
polishing shoes and weapons,

96
00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:19.820
burglary, robbery, fraud, and murder!

97
00:07:19.820 --> 00:07:24.760
And remember, you can never
tell Garp what we make you do!

98
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:29.460
You get one bowl of rice
and one glass of water each day!

99
00:07:29.460 --> 00:07:31.660
That's all I can guarantee you.

100
00:07:31.660 --> 00:07:36.000
You've gotta get everything else
on your own and take care of yourself.

101
00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:36.920
Okay!

102
00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:40.240
"Okay"?! Just like that?! No waterworks?!

103
00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:44.050
This one time, Grandpa threw me into a jungle!

104
00:07:44.050 --> 00:07:48.820
This is a forest, so there's plenty of water to drink
and frogs, snakes and mushrooms to eat!

105
00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:52.950
Plus, I'm gonna be a pirate someday...

106
00:07:52.950 --> 00:07:55.620
so I have to take care of myself!

107
00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:57.230
– Boss!
– Are you alright?!

108
00:07:57.230 --> 00:07:58.620
What are you doing?!

109
00:07:58.620 --> 00:08:01.200
– Heave ho!
– Heave ho!

110
00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:04.160
Where's he headed?

111
00:08:04.160 --> 00:08:05.930
– Heave ho!
– Heave ho!

112
00:08:06.910 --> 00:08:08.200
Where are you going?!

113
00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:10.640
Did you just say "pirate"?

114
00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:12.500
He ignored me!

115
00:08:12.500 --> 00:08:13.770
Hey!

116
00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:22.820
See? I knew he'd be a handful! That's why
I didn't wanna take care of Garp's grandson!

117
00:08:22.820 --> 00:08:24.780
Take it easy, Boss.

118
00:08:25.390 --> 00:08:27.550
Hey!

119
00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:29.090
Wait for me!

120
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.040
Hey!

121
00:08:34.860 --> 00:08:39.960
My name's Luffy! I'm not mad
about you spitting on me anymore!

122
00:08:44.740 --> 00:08:46.510
Why are you laughing?!

123
00:08:46.510 --> 00:08:51.410
He only got some booze on me.
It's nothing worth getting mad over.

124
00:08:51.410 --> 00:08:55.510
It's nothing worth getting
mad over! Let's be friends!

125
00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:56.880
Are you going somewhere?!

126
00:09:04.390 --> 00:09:06.660
It's a dead end!

127
00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:04.000
Hey! Ace is back!

128
00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:05.920
– Food's here!
– Food's here!

129
00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:10.230
Ace, are you by yourself?

130
00:10:10.230 --> 00:10:13.960
Hey, where's Luffy?
I thought he went with you.

131
00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:15.640
Dunno.

132
00:10:16.900 --> 00:10:19.500
Get it together, Boss!

133
00:10:19.500 --> 00:10:20.700
What'd you say?!

134
00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:24.140
I'm saying it's really bad that
we lost him on the first day!

135
00:10:24.140 --> 00:10:27.970
Leave me alone! If he dies, he dies!

136
00:10:28.650 --> 00:10:33.190
I've already given up on Ace, too!

137
00:10:33.960 --> 00:10:39.300
Even if he winds up dead somewhere,
all I have to do is tell Garp it was an accident.

138
00:10:39.300 --> 00:10:43.360
As they say, "The devil's children
have the devil's luck."

139
00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:45.670
He's demon spawn!

140
00:10:46.420 --> 00:10:52.710
If the government finds out that he's here,
what do you think they'd do to us?!

141
00:10:52.710 --> 00:10:54.500
Take it easy, Boss.

142
00:10:54.500 --> 00:10:58.480
You're drinking too much!

143
00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:02.450
One Week Later...

144
00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:02.450
One week later...

145
00:11:03.100 --> 00:11:05.290
Boss! Boss Dadan!

146
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:06.910
Who– Huh?!

147
00:11:06.910 --> 00:11:08.550
Who is it...? Huh?!

148
00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:09.720
It's you!

149
00:11:09.720 --> 00:11:13.030
Luffy came back!

150
00:11:18.040 --> 00:11:19.410
Why, you...!

151
00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:22.870
You survived, you little sh–

152
00:11:22.870 --> 00:11:24.530
Take it easy, Boss.

153
00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:26.820
Where were you?!

154
00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:30.180
Take it easy! Where were you
and what were you doing?

155
00:11:30.640 --> 00:11:34.050
Wolves were chasing me through the ravine.

156
00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:37.320
What were you doing in the ravine?!

157
00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:43.220
Anyway, good thing you're okay.

158
00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:43.990
Yeah, it's good.

159
00:11:43.990 --> 00:11:45.050
Like hell it's good!

160
00:11:45.050 --> 00:11:48.060
The pest came back!

161
00:11:48.930 --> 00:11:53.890
Just go to bed already! I'll start
working you like a dog tomorrow!

162
00:11:53.890 --> 00:11:54.840
Already?!

163
00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:04.900
Morning!

164
00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:07.780
Where you off to today, Ace?

165
00:12:07.780 --> 00:12:11.570
Take me with you! Let's be friends!

166
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:13.620
Wait up!

167
00:12:13.620 --> 00:12:16.160
Boss! He's chasing after Ace again!

168
00:12:16.750 --> 00:12:20.250
Hey! You've got chores to do!

169
00:12:21.880 --> 00:12:25.060
No way!

170
00:12:25.070 --> 00:12:27.460
You're out of control, you little turd!

171
00:12:27.460 --> 00:12:28.880
Take it eas–

172
00:12:28.880 --> 00:12:30.870
Bring him back right now!

173
00:12:30.870 --> 00:12:31.500
Yes, ma'am.

174
00:12:31.510 --> 00:12:33.600
Hey!

175
00:12:51.150 --> 00:12:53.730
Even though he always lost track of Ace....

176
00:12:57.260 --> 00:12:59.320
he kept chasing him day after day.

177
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:00.490
Ace!

178
00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:10.870
For one month...

179
00:13:12.210 --> 00:13:13.610
For two months...

180
00:13:13.740 --> 00:13:15.460
Ace!

181
00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:16.610
No matter the rain...

182
00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:19.200
No matter the wind...

183
00:13:21.460 --> 00:13:23.350
Ace!

184
00:13:23.350 --> 00:13:27.060
Luffy was relentless in his pursuit of Ace.

185
00:13:33.160 --> 00:13:35.440
Ace!

186
00:13:43.380 --> 00:13:47.080
Ace! Hey!

187
00:13:47.080 --> 00:13:50.850
I can't believe he followed me
all the way here. He's so persistent.

188
00:13:52.790 --> 00:13:54.000
Oh, crap!

189
00:13:54.890 --> 00:13:59.550
Damn! I lost him again! Ace sure is quick!

190
00:14:00.660 --> 00:14:01.390
That you, Ace?!

191
00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:15.010
That's the beast of Mt. Colubo!
No one can beat that thing!

192
00:14:17.580 --> 00:14:20.150
Why won't he run?! It's gonna eat him!

193
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:24.280
M-My legs w-won't move!

194
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:26.170
Tch! That twerp!

195
00:15:29.720 --> 00:15:34.540
After three months of cuts,
bruises, and endless pursuit...

196
00:15:41.630 --> 00:15:43.780
It's the edge of the forest.

197
00:15:49.390 --> 00:15:52.240
Whoa! What is this place?!

198
00:15:53.490 --> 00:15:58.790
North of Mt. Colubo, where the Dadan
Family resides, lies a neglected place.

199
00:15:59.700 --> 00:16:05.150
Smoke endlessly emanates from
heaps of discarded trash.

200
00:16:05.150 --> 00:16:08.620
Unwanted things accumulate here.

201
00:16:09.520 --> 00:16:15.100
Its inhabitants are outlaws,
shunned by mainstream society.

202
00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:18.000
Naturally, the law holds no sway here.

203
00:16:18.710 --> 00:16:22.720
Without so much as a doctor,
the area teems with crime and disease.

204
00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:26.830
This is the Gray Terminal.

205
00:16:26.830 --> 00:16:28.850
Come on out, treasure...

206
00:16:28.850 --> 00:16:31.650
Isn't there anything worth selling around here?

207
00:16:33.940 --> 00:16:35.830
I got something!

208
00:16:35.830 --> 00:16:37.050
They're mine!

209
00:16:37.050 --> 00:16:38.840
No, they're mine!

210
00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:40.710
Lay off! I found them!

211
00:16:40.710 --> 00:16:43.000
Hands off the goods, you vultures!

212
00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:45.730
I'm gonna sell them in town!

213
00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:46.720
Like hell you will!

214
00:16:46.720 --> 00:16:48.390
Get back here!

215
00:16:57.350 --> 00:16:58.330
Damn you!

216
00:16:58.330 --> 00:16:59.010
Drop 'em!

217
00:17:01.140 --> 00:17:05.860
If you'd just handed 'em over,
I wouldn't have needed to sock you!

218
00:17:06.650 --> 00:17:08.670
Nice going!

219
00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:10.680
Why, you...! Are you kidding me?!

220
00:17:13.460 --> 00:17:15.290
Thief!

221
00:17:21.310 --> 00:17:22.250
Move it, kid!

222
00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:27.520
Hurry it up! Move or I'll...

223
00:17:27.520 --> 00:17:29.870
He went that way!

224
00:17:35.490 --> 00:17:37.550
Sabo! Sabo, are you there?

225
00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:42.020
Oh, Ace!

226
00:17:42.590 --> 00:17:44.570
Sorry I'm late.

227
00:17:44.570 --> 00:17:46.160
You sure are!

228
00:17:46.490 --> 00:17:49.480
I already finished a job in town.

229
00:17:46.780 --> 00:17:51.290
Sabo (Age 10)
(A Boy Living in the Gray Terminal)

230
00:17:52.360 --> 00:17:55.200
Oh, yeah? Truth is, so did I.

231
00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:57.000
– Same time!
– Same time!

232
00:17:57.000 --> 00:18:00.630
Whoa! That's a lot...! A lot more than I made!

233
00:18:00.630 --> 00:18:03.800
What a haul! How'd you pull it off?!

234
00:18:03.810 --> 00:18:07.400
I stole it from some thugs near the Great Gate.

235
00:18:07.400 --> 00:18:10.670
Damn! You win again!

236
00:18:10.670 --> 00:18:12.660
It doesn't matter who wins, does it?

237
00:18:14.010 --> 00:18:16.620
This pirate fund is for the both of us.

238
00:18:16.620 --> 00:18:19.660
It's been five years
since we started saving, huh?

239
00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:23.730
We've worked hard.

240
00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:26.700
We sure have!

241
00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:32.490
To leave the East Blue and sail into a world
these island hicks couldn't even dream of...

242
00:18:32.500 --> 00:18:35.240
it just gets me so pumped!

243
00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:45.510
Hurry and close the lid.
You never know who's watching.

244
00:18:45.510 --> 00:18:49.870
How much do you think
we'll need for a pirate ship?

245
00:18:49.870 --> 00:18:53.710
Who knows? Hundreds of thousands,
or maybe even millions...

246
00:18:53.710 --> 00:18:55.310
We'll get there one day.

247
00:18:55.310 --> 00:18:56.790
"A pirate ship"?!

248
00:18:57.390 --> 00:19:01.360
Are you guys gonna be pirates?!

249
00:19:01.360 --> 00:19:03.800
I'm gonna be one too!

250
00:19:03.800 --> 00:19:05.030
Hey!

251
00:19:14.870 --> 00:19:16.120
– Be quiet!
– Be quiet!

252
00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:23.640
Ace! This is where you've
been going every day?!

253
00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:24.840
Shut up.

254
00:19:24.840 --> 00:19:28.680
So this is that Luffy kid you told me about.

255
00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:31.320
Oh, you told him about me?!

256
00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:33.850
I complained about how persistent you are.

257
00:19:33.850 --> 00:19:37.390
And about how airheaded you seem!

258
00:19:38.420 --> 00:19:39.420
I see!

259
00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:42.670
Doesn't he get that we're insulting him?

260
00:19:42.670 --> 00:19:45.640
He finally made it all the way here.

261
00:19:45.640 --> 00:19:48.540
I even made sure to avoid the main pathways.

262
00:19:48.540 --> 00:19:52.880
Are you Ace's friend?! Be my friend, too!

263
00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:56.550
Shut up! We don't even know each other!

264
00:19:56.550 --> 00:19:58.400
Then, what's your name?

265
00:19:58.400 --> 00:19:59.200
Sa–

266
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:00.040
I'm not telling!

267
00:20:00.820 --> 00:20:04.050
This is why I told you to live here with me!

268
00:20:04.050 --> 00:20:08.750
Your daily round trip "training" through
the mountains was a bad idea after all!

269
00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:10.010
What do we do?

270
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:13.640
Now he knows our secret.

271
00:20:13.640 --> 00:20:16.660
He'll spill the beans if we don't do something.

272
00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:24.300
We gotta kill him.

273
00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:26.200
Alright, let's do it.

274
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.290
Wha...?!

275
00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:30.380
What?!

276
00:20:31.090 --> 00:20:36.880
Don't kill me! Someone save me!
I don't wanna die!

277
00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:38.820
You idiot! Be quiet!

278
00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:41.290
Sabo! Hurry and do it!

279
00:20:41.290 --> 00:20:43.220
Why me?! You do it!

280
00:20:43.220 --> 00:20:45.540
I've never killed anyone before!

281
00:20:45.540 --> 00:20:48.470
Neither have I! I don't know how to do it!

282
00:20:48.470 --> 00:20:51.410
Please don't throw me into water!

283
00:20:51.410 --> 00:20:52.850
Right! The river!

284
00:20:52.850 --> 00:20:55.300
Why'd he give that away?!

285
00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:56.330
'Cause he's a moron!

286
00:20:56.330 --> 00:20:58.870
Somebody help me!

287
00:20:58.870 --> 00:21:00.520
– Shut up!
– Shut up!

288
00:21:02.710 --> 00:21:03.740
I don't wanna die! No!

289
00:21:03.740 --> 00:21:05.560
I don't wanna die! No!

290
00:21:05.560 --> 00:21:07.680
There's a voice coming from the forest!

291
00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:08.810
A kid's voice!

292
00:21:08.810 --> 00:21:11.120
Oh, no! Someone's coming!

293
00:21:11.120 --> 00:21:13.480
Let's just untie him!

294
00:21:13.480 --> 00:21:16.190
If we don't clear out, they'll find our treasure!

295
00:21:18.910 --> 00:21:22.560
Those brats, Ace and Sabo,
are infamous around these parts.

296
00:21:23.590 --> 00:21:28.340
Porchemy
Bluejam Pirates

297
00:21:23.600 --> 00:21:25.890
You're absolutely certain

298
00:21:25.890 --> 00:21:28.350
it was Ace who swiped the cash, right?

299
00:21:28.350 --> 00:21:32.470
Yeah... It's embarrassing, but we got sloppy.

300
00:21:32.470 --> 00:21:35.080
I can't believe that kid...

301
00:21:35.080 --> 00:21:38.020
laying his hands on our crew's loot!

302
00:21:38.660 --> 00:21:43.660
If Captain Bluejam hears
about this, we're all dead!

303
00:21:45.320 --> 00:21:50.090
Damn it! Those thugs were Bluejam's lackeys?

304
00:21:50.090 --> 00:21:53.100
Thugs? You mean you got
that money from those guys?

305
00:21:53.810 --> 00:21:56.630
We've got some dangerous
money on our hands...

306
00:21:56.640 --> 00:22:00.640
He has a real sword...
Porchemy is one of Bluejam's goons.

307
00:22:01.380 --> 00:22:04.410
He's crazy. Have you heard?

308
00:22:05.480 --> 00:22:09.650
When he beats someone, he scalps them alive!

309
00:22:13.540 --> 00:22:16.320
Let's hope they just move along...

310
00:22:17.820 --> 00:22:19.360
Huh? Where'd he go?

311
00:22:22.130 --> 00:22:26.120
Let go of me! What are you doing?

312
00:22:23.970 --> 00:22:26.140
– How'd he get caught?!
– How'd he get caught?!

313
00:22:26.800 --> 00:22:28.450
Who's this little shit?

314
00:22:28.450 --> 00:22:29.640
Help me!

315
00:22:29.640 --> 00:22:31.260
Ace!

316
00:22:32.820 --> 00:22:34.630
Help me, Ace!

317
00:22:34.630 --> 00:22:39.000
You dumbass...!
Shouting my name like that...!
Ace! Ace! Ace!

318
00:22:40.170 --> 00:22:42.120
Did you just say "Ace"?

319
00:22:43.420 --> 00:22:44.190
Yeah, so?!

320
00:22:44.190 --> 00:22:47.390
Do you know Ace?

321
00:22:48.860 --> 00:22:50.200
He's my friend!

322
00:22:51.110 --> 00:22:53.700
Oh, but he was going to kill me just now.

323
00:22:55.360 --> 00:22:58.270
Just. Stop. Talking.

324
00:22:58.820 --> 00:23:00.690
I need to ask...

325
00:23:00.690 --> 00:23:05.970
Earlier today, Ace stole
some of our money and ran off.

326
00:23:05.970 --> 00:23:09.210
You wouldn't happen to know
where he put it, would you?

327
00:23:13.140 --> 00:23:16.840
Oh, crap! They're gonna take our treasure!

328
00:23:16.840 --> 00:23:19.180
That airhead better not blab...

329
00:23:26.460 --> 00:23:27.260
– What?!
– What?!

330
00:23:27.260 --> 00:23:28.650
Huh?!

331
00:23:28.650 --> 00:23:31.600
I-I don't know...

332
00:23:32.560 --> 00:23:34.170
What a terrible liar!

333
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:42.470
All right, all right. If you
don't know, then that's that.

334
00:23:45.600 --> 00:23:49.250
I'll help jog your memory, so don't worry!

335
00:23:50.520 --> 00:23:53.540
What the hell?! Let me go!
Where are you taking me?!

336
00:23:53.540 --> 00:23:56.390
Damn it! Idiot! Let go of me!

337
00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:57.420
You bastard!

338
00:23:58.150 --> 00:23:59.670
What do we do?

339
00:23:59.670 --> 00:24:02.400
"What do we do?" Well...

340
00:24:10.740 --> 00:24:12.600
Let me go!

341
00:24:12.600 --> 00:24:14.410
I'm not telling you anything!

342
00:24:22.720 --> 00:24:24.750
You little shit!

343
00:24:38.840 --> 00:24:42.430
I tried to tell you, but I'm all rubbery
after eating the Gum-Gum Fruit!

344
00:24:42.700 --> 00:24:44.330
Quiet!

345
00:24:45.510 --> 00:24:47.650
A devil fruit, huh?

346
00:24:49.080 --> 00:24:51.240
Yeah, you're the genuine article.

347
00:24:53.620 --> 00:24:55.170
Get my gloves.

348
00:24:55.170 --> 00:24:57.150
Wha...?! Y-Yes, sir!

349
00:24:57.150 --> 00:25:01.350
Hurry up! Hurry up! We're screwed
if Porchemy and his goons come back!

350
00:25:01.350 --> 00:25:04.550
We've gotta move the treasure fast!

351
00:25:04.560 --> 00:25:08.320
It's only a matter of time before
that Luffy kid rats us out!

352
00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:11.690
If they find this, they won't just
take back what we stole from them,

353
00:25:11.690 --> 00:25:15.890
but the entire pirate fund
from over the past five years!

354
00:25:21.350 --> 00:25:23.370
Listen, you little shit.

355
00:25:23.370 --> 00:25:29.070
The cash that your friend Ace stole
was important to our pirate crew...

356
00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:32.380
and you know where it is!

357
00:25:32.380 --> 00:25:34.880
So, you will tell me.

358
00:25:36.260 --> 00:25:37.050
I won't!

359
00:25:45.790 --> 00:25:46.770
That's gotta hurt!

360
00:25:50.930 --> 00:25:53.900
You shouldn't piss off a pirate!

361
00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:59.040
Our captain, Bluejam, is a brutal monster!

362
00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:09.110
That hurt! I'm scared!

363
00:26:09.110 --> 00:26:10.750
Somebody save me!

364
00:26:13.050 --> 00:26:15.920
You guys, find Ace and Sabo!

365
00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:18.520
Don't just stand there twiddling your thumbs!

366
00:26:18.520 --> 00:26:19.330
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

367
00:26:27.950 --> 00:26:31.010
You're asking about Ace and Sabo?

368
00:26:31.010 --> 00:26:33.900
You must be delinquents from the city.

369
00:26:34.800 --> 00:26:37.750
You're better off not getting
involved with those two.

370
00:26:38.620 --> 00:26:41.310
Don't underestimate 'em
just 'cause they're puny.

371
00:26:41.310 --> 00:26:44.280
Those mad dogs turn tigers into mincemeat!

372
00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:47.570
Ace and Sabo, huh? Haven't seen 'em...

373
00:26:48.240 --> 00:26:50.840
But more importantly, fellas...

374
00:26:50.840 --> 00:26:52.960
why don't you hand over your valuables?

375
00:26:53.300 --> 00:26:55.490
W-We'd rather not!

376
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:57.470
Let's go look somewhere else!

377
00:27:00.630 --> 00:27:02.200
It's almost nighttime...

378
00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:05.310
Alright! All done!

379
00:27:05.310 --> 00:27:07.650
We moved all the treasure!

380
00:27:11.460 --> 00:27:13.100
Ace!

381
00:27:13.100 --> 00:27:15.000
Sabo, what's wrong?

382
00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:17.050
Were they looting our old hideout?

383
00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:22.220
No, they never showed.

384
00:27:22.240 --> 00:27:24.120
And I bet they won't!

385
00:27:25.010 --> 00:27:25.920
Meaning...?

386
00:27:25.920 --> 00:27:28.330
That Luffy kid...

387
00:27:29.360 --> 00:27:31.660
still hasn't told them a thing!

388
00:27:33.260 --> 00:27:36.160
He's definitely being tortured.

389
00:27:36.160 --> 00:27:40.410
He was such an idiot crybaby that
I thought for sure he'd tell them!

390
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:41.670
I don't get it!

391
00:27:43.770 --> 00:27:45.380
At this rate, he'll...

392
00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:57.230
Pirate Bay
Gray Terminal

393
00:27:54.390 --> 00:27:56.660
They're late...

394
00:27:57.220 --> 00:27:59.700
Who was in charge today?

395
00:28:00.590 --> 00:28:03.890
It was Porchemy, Captain Bluejam.

396
00:28:04.610 --> 00:28:06.860
The sun's already setting.

397
00:28:10.570 --> 00:28:14.000
There's no way it takes this long
to cash in the goods.

398
00:28:14.770 --> 00:28:18.970
You don't think he'd run away with the money, do you?

399
00:28:14.970 --> 00:28:18.970
Captain Bluejam
Bluejam Pirates

400
00:28:18.970 --> 00:28:21.050
No, he'd never...!

401
00:28:21.050 --> 00:28:24.050
He wouldn't risk his life to pull a stunt like that.

402
00:28:26.140 --> 00:28:27.990
You're right.

403
00:28:32.690 --> 00:28:35.760
Spit it out already...!

404
00:28:38.100 --> 00:28:41.130
Ah... P-P-Porchemy...!

405
00:28:41.770 --> 00:28:43.470
It's no use!

406
00:28:46.780 --> 00:28:50.040
He's too worn out to even scream now!

407
00:28:54.680 --> 00:28:57.250
He probably won't tell us anything,

408
00:28:57.250 --> 00:29:00.440
and, to be honest, this is
so brutal I can barely watch!

409
00:29:00.440 --> 00:29:03.250
Let's just let him go!

410
00:29:05.700 --> 00:29:09.760
If you have the time to worry about the kid,
then go find Ace and Sabo!

411
00:29:09.760 --> 00:29:14.100
We're the ones who'll get killed!
Don't you get it?!

412
00:29:14.100 --> 00:29:19.740
The scheduled drop-off with
Captain Bluejam is long overdue!

413
00:29:24.500 --> 00:29:26.250
Poor kiddo...

414
00:29:26.250 --> 00:29:28.480
Should we get the town sheriff involved?

415
00:29:28.480 --> 00:29:29.990
It won't do any good.

416
00:29:29.990 --> 00:29:32.780
The country's laws don't extend to this area.

417
00:29:32.780 --> 00:29:37.020
Besides, that guy is on Bluejam's crew.

418
00:29:37.040 --> 00:29:39.360
They pay off the nobles!

419
00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:44.370
Whatever crimes they commit in this country
—even murder—will just be overlooked!

420
00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:49.810
No matter how many corpses pile up
around here, nobody pays any mind!

421
00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:53.000
Just tell me!

422
00:29:54.070 --> 00:29:55.680
I won't!

423
00:29:56.310 --> 00:30:01.380
You little shit! You're putting too
much effort into keeping this secret!

424
00:30:05.160 --> 00:30:07.770
Spit it out!

425
00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:11.790
I won't.

426
00:30:12.640 --> 00:30:13.990
I won't!

427
00:30:14.650 --> 00:30:16.270
I won't!

428
00:30:19.810 --> 00:30:21.620
I won't!

429
00:30:24.120 --> 00:30:26.070
Fine. Enough.

430
00:30:44.720 --> 00:30:46.150
Die.

431
00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:52.380
Stop!                                     Stop!

432
00:30:57.800 --> 00:30:58.700
Outta my way!

433
00:31:01.810 --> 00:31:04.340
That's the kid, Porchemy!

434
00:31:04.340 --> 00:31:06.980
He's the one who stole our money, dammit!

435
00:31:06.980 --> 00:31:08.050
What?

436
00:31:08.050 --> 00:31:10.310
A-Ace!

437
00:31:15.760 --> 00:31:19.500
You saved us time by coming here yourselves!

438
00:31:19.500 --> 00:31:23.510
We were having a hard time
making your friend talk.

439
00:31:23.510 --> 00:31:24.540
Ace!

440
00:31:24.540 --> 00:31:26.820
L-Let me go!

441
00:31:26.820 --> 00:31:28.440
Sabo!

442
00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:33.500
– Porchemy!
– Porchemy!

443
00:31:36.110 --> 00:31:38.510
Ace! Sabo!

444
00:31:38.510 --> 00:31:42.050
That kinda hurt, y'know? Hey...!

445
00:31:43.970 --> 00:31:47.960
Do you know what happens
when you mess with grown-ups?!

446
00:31:48.650 --> 00:31:50.450
I'm the one you're going to fight!

447
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:52.260
Sabo! Grab the kid!

448
00:31:52.260 --> 00:31:53.360
Ace!

449
00:31:54.520 --> 00:31:57.530
He has a sword! Be careful!

450
00:32:10.040 --> 00:32:11.340
Oh, my knife!

451
00:32:11.800 --> 00:32:13.480
Porchemy, that kid...!

452
00:32:16.950 --> 00:32:18.950
Let's go, Ace!

453
00:32:18.950 --> 00:32:20.280
You go on ahead!

454
00:32:20.980 --> 00:32:23.350
You're crazy! Hurry up!

455
00:32:23.920 --> 00:32:25.830
When I face someone...

456
00:32:25.830 --> 00:32:28.130
I never run!

457
00:32:28.130 --> 00:32:30.740
What'd you say?! You little shit!

458
00:32:30.740 --> 00:32:34.330
Don't do it! He's not like the thugs in the city!

459
00:32:34.330 --> 00:32:36.700
Your friend gets it!

460
00:32:36.700 --> 00:32:39.410
Now... playtime is over.

461
00:32:39.410 --> 00:32:44.550
It's our money after all,
so give it back nice and easy, kid!

462
00:32:44.550 --> 00:32:47.050
You probably stole it on impulse, right?

463
00:32:47.050 --> 00:32:50.110
Just give the money back before you regret it.

464
00:32:52.470 --> 00:32:55.390
We can put that money
to better use than you!

465
00:32:56.450 --> 00:32:57.170
Wha...?

466
00:32:58.510 --> 00:33:00.260
What the hell did you say?!

467
00:33:00.560 --> 00:33:02.430
Wait here a minute!

468
00:33:03.890 --> 00:33:06.330
Enough of your crap!

469
00:33:10.630 --> 00:33:14.940
If I lose to a couple of kids,
I may as well quit being a pirate!

470
00:33:14.940 --> 00:33:17.770
– Then you're gonna quit!
– Then you're gonna quit!

471
00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:20.010
You're all dead!

472
00:33:28.820 --> 00:33:32.330
I heard the whole story, Porchemy...

473
00:33:32.330 --> 00:33:34.030
How pathetic.

474
00:33:34.030 --> 00:33:37.290
You seriously let a couple of kids beat you?

475
00:33:38.240 --> 00:33:42.920
I'm sorry, Captain Bluejam... The money is–

476
00:33:42.920 --> 00:33:45.710
Don't look at me! You're a disgrace!

477
00:33:57.430 --> 00:34:00.060
That's a real bad habit, Ace!

478
00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:03.980
When faced with a real pirate, it's best to run!

479
00:34:03.980 --> 00:34:06.120
Why do you have such a death wish?

480
00:34:06.120 --> 00:34:10.460
It's just not the same.
I liked the last one better.

481
00:34:12.030 --> 00:34:14.030
We really stepped in it this time...

482
00:34:14.030 --> 00:34:17.900
The Bluejam crew isn't going to let this slide.

483
00:34:17.900 --> 00:34:19.340
They'll come for us.

484
00:34:19.340 --> 00:34:23.270
That was so scary!
I thought I was gonna die!

485
00:34:27.140 --> 00:34:31.060
You're so annoying! Shut up!
Stop crying already!

486
00:34:31.060 --> 00:34:34.350
I really can't stand cowards and crybabies!

487
00:34:37.630 --> 00:34:39.230
Th-Thank you!

488
00:34:42.830 --> 00:34:43.880
You...

489
00:34:45.130 --> 00:34:47.130
You saved me!

490
00:34:47.130 --> 00:34:48.370
You...!

491
00:34:48.370 --> 00:34:50.930
Whoa, let him show some gratitude.

492
00:34:54.390 --> 00:34:58.400
Why didn't you just
tell them what you knew?!

493
00:34:58.400 --> 00:35:02.220
They'd even kill women
and children without hesitation!

494
00:35:03.190 --> 00:35:07.830
I thought if I said anything...
you wouldn't be my friend.

495
00:35:08.490 --> 00:35:10.860
It's better than dying, isn't it?

496
00:35:10.860 --> 00:35:13.360
Why are you so obsessed
with being my friend?!

497
00:35:15.620 --> 00:35:17.160
Because...

498
00:35:17.160 --> 00:35:21.660
Haven't I been giving you a hard time?

499
00:35:21.660 --> 00:35:24.190
Why would you follow me this far?

500
00:35:29.860 --> 00:35:31.170
Because...

501
00:35:32.210 --> 00:35:35.320
Because I don't have anyone else!

502
00:35:36.040 --> 00:35:40.000
I can't go back to Windmill Village
and I hate mountain bandits!

503
00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:43.480
If I didn't follow you, I'd be all alone!

504
00:35:43.480 --> 00:35:46.730
Being lonely is more painful than getting hurt!

505
00:35:48.460 --> 00:35:50.590
Where are your parents?

506
00:35:50.590 --> 00:35:52.330
Grandpa is all I have.

507
00:35:54.460 --> 00:35:56.930
So you feel better when I'm around?

508
00:35:56.140 --> 00:35:56.930
Uh-huh.

509
00:35:57.940 --> 00:36:00.570
You need me?

510
00:35:59.670 --> 00:36:00.570
Uh-huh.

511
00:36:03.520 --> 00:36:06.260
"What if Gold Roger had a child?"

512
00:36:07.410 --> 00:36:10.110
We definitely don't need a kid like that around!

513
00:36:10.110 --> 00:36:15.750
Demon spawn like that doesn't
even deserve to be alive!

514
00:36:21.280 --> 00:36:22.680
Do you want me...

515
00:36:23.630 --> 00:36:24.830
to live?

516
00:36:28.200 --> 00:36:29.660
Of course I do!

517
00:36:31.010 --> 00:36:31.940
Okay...

518
00:36:34.720 --> 00:36:39.080
but I hate spoiled brats like you.

519
00:36:40.990 --> 00:36:44.120
I'm not a spoiled brat! I'm tough!

520
00:36:44.120 --> 00:36:48.650
Tough?! You're not tough at all!
Men aren't supposed to cry!

521
00:36:48.650 --> 00:36:53.300
Have you ever been hit
with spikes? I'm only seven!

522
00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:58.320
When I'm ten like you,
I'll be super strong and never ever cry!

523
00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:02.270
I never cried when I was seven,
you dork! Don't compare us!

524
00:37:02.270 --> 00:37:05.440
I'm gonna be stronger than anyone!

525
00:37:05.440 --> 00:37:09.490
I promised Shanks that
I'd become a great pirate!

526
00:37:09.490 --> 00:37:10.980
A pirate? You?

527
00:37:10.980 --> 00:37:11.610
Yes!

528
00:37:11.610 --> 00:37:12.780
– No way!
– Yes way!

529
00:37:14.560 --> 00:37:16.320
Okay, that's enough!

530
00:37:17.660 --> 00:37:21.990
Hey, by the way, I have a little problem.

531
00:37:21.990 --> 00:37:23.090
What? A problem?

532
00:37:23.090 --> 00:37:24.090
Mm-hmm...

533
00:37:24.090 --> 00:37:29.730
I've been living in this forest, but it's
too close to that hideout in Pirate Bay.

534
00:37:29.730 --> 00:37:34.660
What if they attack me when I'm
exhausted and fast asleep?

535
00:37:35.910 --> 00:37:38.040
That's why I need your help.

536
00:37:53.680 --> 00:37:58.190
How did they get hurt?
They're all bandaged up!

537
00:38:00.410 --> 00:38:02.170
Hey, that's...

538
00:38:06.630 --> 00:38:10.200
Whoa! Boss! Boss! We have a problem!

539
00:38:10.200 --> 00:38:12.780
Huh? It's too early to "have a problem"...

540
00:38:12.780 --> 00:38:16.750
Whoa! What's going on here?!

541
00:38:16.750 --> 00:38:18.780
One, two...

542
00:38:19.860 --> 00:38:21.380
Huh?

543
00:38:21.380 --> 00:38:24.790
Ace! Luffy! Who is that?!

544
00:38:26.130 --> 00:38:27.830
Who is who?

545
00:38:30.690 --> 00:38:33.990
Why is there one more kid?!

546
00:38:33.990 --> 00:38:35.260
Who the hell are you?!

547
00:38:35.990 --> 00:38:37.670
Are you talking about me?

548
00:38:39.110 --> 00:38:42.430
I'm Sabo! Hey, you must be Dadan!

549
00:38:42.430 --> 00:38:45.710
Sabo? I've heard your name before!

550
00:38:45.710 --> 00:38:50.270
Oh, yeah? That makes it easier!
Thank you for taking me in!

551
00:38:51.270 --> 00:38:54.950
I heard you're a shitty a brat just like them!

552
00:38:54.950 --> 00:38:58.580
Well, sure! And I heard that you're
a no-good, annoying old hag!

553
00:39:09.080 --> 00:39:11.390
Ace! Luffy! Sabo!

554
00:39:11.390 --> 00:39:15.430
I'm giving you three a place to stay,
so get to work already!

555
00:39:16.930 --> 00:39:19.110
Thank you, Dadan!

556
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:35.850
After being forced to leave the Gray Terminal,
Ace's best friend Sabo moved in.

557
00:39:37.240 --> 00:39:40.080
Ace, Sabo, and Luffy...

558
00:39:41.090 --> 00:39:46.860
The trio soon began to spend their time
fighting wildlife in the mountains and jungle.

559
00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:51.400
They also clashed with hooligans
from the city and pirates at the bay.

560
00:39:51.400 --> 00:39:58.940
Eventually, their notoriety spread
even to the heart of the kingdom!
